# Branch policy: do not commit to main

In this repo (**mnemospark-backend**), **do not make commits or apply changes directly on `main`**.

- **Always** create a new branch for any code or config change (e.g. `fix/description`, `feat/description`).
- Check out the new branch before editing (e.g. `git checkout -b fix/my-fix`).
- Commit and push the branch, then open a PR for review and merge.
- Leave `main` unchanged locally; only merge via PR (or equivalent) after review.

This keeps `main` stable and ensures all changes are reviewed before they reach the default branch.
